The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Two found hanging
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Two found hanging
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A newly-wed woman and jobless middle-aged man were found hanging in their homes in Howrah on Wednesday.         
	Sova Sau was hanging from the ceiling of her bedroom in her Badamtala home. The 29-year-olds family members complained at Domjur police station that her in-laws used to torture her for dowry. Sovas husband Rabin Sau, 35, his mother and his sister were arrested.        
	An investigator said: Sova Saus relatives alleged that she was murdered by her in-laws. We have arrested three people in this connection and started a case against them under Section 498 of IPC. They will be produced before the chief judicial magistrates court in Howrah tomorrow.         
	According to the police, Sova and Rabin married three months ago. Relations between them soured soon after. She used to be beaten up and tortured for dowry.         
	Sital Chandra Bose, 40, was found hanging from the ceiling of a balcony in his Tinkari Halder Lane house under Golabari police station.        
	The police have started an unnatural death case and sent the body for post-mortem.         
	An investigator said Bose had become depressed after years of financial problems. He was jobless for several years and had also become an alcoholic.        
	On Wednesday morning, neighbours saw him hanging from the balcony and alerted his family members.                                                                                                                                                                         
